Experiment 1

Some info on the models

Model Original: q_2 = q_7, q_3 = q_6 & r_3 = r_6 (all but highest confidence response mapping of uncertainty states equated and lowest two confidence response mapping of detection states equated)
Q restricted: q_2 = q_7, q_3 = q_6 (all but highest confidence response mapping of uncertainty states equated)
R restricted: r_3 = r_6 (lowest two confidence response mapping of detection states equated)

Some info on convergence

For Model Original

Two approaches failed:
partial, TreeBUGS, trait
partial, TreeBUGS, beta

Frequentist approach with complete pooling had no convergence problems (asymptotic.complete.MPTinR).

Bayesian approach with no pooling (simple.no.TreeBUGS) had 3 parameters with Rhat > 1.05.
Bayesian approach with complete pooling (simple.complete.TreeBUGS) converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.
Bayesian approach with partial pooling (trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.

For Q restricted

One approach failed: partial, TreeBUGS, beta

Bayesian approach with no pooling (simple.no.TreeBUGS) had 4 parameters with Rhat > 1.05.
Bayesian approach with complete pooling (simple.complete.TreeBUGS) had 2 parameters with Rhat > 1.05.
Bayesian approach with partial pooling (trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) had 53 parameters with Rhat > 1.05 but uncorrelated (trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) had one parameter with Rhat > 1.05.

For R restricted

One approach failed: partial, TreeBUGS, beta

Frequentist approach with complete pooling had no convergence problems (asymptotic.complete.MPTinR).

Bayesian approach with no pooling (simple.no.TreeBUGS) had 54 parameters with Rhat > 1.05.
Bayesian approach with complete pooling (simple.complete.TreeBUGS) converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.
Bayesian approach with partial pooling (trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) had 8 parameters with Rhat > 1.05 but uncorrelated (trait_uncorrelated.partial.TreeBUGS) converged well, all Rhat < 1.05.
